<subSubSection id="C005895942BEFE83BF1DCA3ADB9FD235" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="40D5818FE671DC7CEDFA605228D9C127" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="94FD167C6EBCBAFC3489EE5A7B5C47E2" pageId="3" pageNumber="138">
The shell morphology of the present specimens compare very well to 
<taxonomicName id="6614CB2038313996EA33440C04D1EEB7" authority="" authorityName="" class="Gastropoda" family="Scolodontidae" genus="Prohappia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prohappia besckei" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="besckei">Prohappia besckei</taxonomicName>
; the size of the specimens from 
<normalizedToken id="B135437F1392DB1D823DFD7ABA505F09" originalValue="Goiás">Goias</normalizedToken>
, however, is much smaller (D ~ 2 mm), slightly larger than half the normal size. This could represent a variation of the species in a cave environment, but the sample is too small to be of any significance. The present record extends the species distribution ca. 600 km to the north.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
